{
  "_comment": [
    "Maps each ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code to its default DeCloud region.",
    "Used by install.sh's auto-suggest: when the operator's country is detected",
    "from IP, install.sh suggests the matching region as the default for the",
    "Region prompt. Operators can always override.",
    "",
    "Edge cases (decided choices, see LOCALITY.md for reasoning):",
    "  TR → eu-east   (NATO/CoE alignment, European peering density)",
    "  RU → eu-east   (Eastern European network topology)",
    "  IL → me-west   (Mediterranean ME peering)",
    "  EG → me-west   (peering favours ME over Africa)",
    "  CY → eu-east   (EU member; Mediterranean cable landings)",
    "  MX → na-central (NAFTA peering)",
    "  AU → oceania   (distinct submarine cable topology)",
    "  IS → eu-north  (transatlantic cable landing)",
    "  GE/AM/AZ → eu-east (Caucasus, grouped with EE)",
    "",
    "Territories without independent network presence (BV, HM, AQ, GS, TF) are",
    "mapped to the most plausible parent region but in practice will never",
    "have a node deployed there."
  ],

